        "created_at": "2022-01-16T00:56:50.200Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Is it possible to add LaTeX mathematical functionality inside signal messages?</p>\n<p>I think it would be a great feature. That can greatly simplify messaging between students and academics. And because of that, it could be an optional feature, not enabled by default.</p>\n<p>It could be achieved with e.g. <a href=\"https://github.com/KaTeX/KaTeX\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">KaTeX project</a>, which is also written in JavaScript.</p>\n<p>Semantic proposition:<br>\n\\tex$2^5$<br>\n\\tex$\\sqrt{5}$</p>",
