        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/herohtar/{size}/43780_2.png",
        "created_at": "2022-01-16T01:04:58.569Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"WiktorOgrodnik\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"40878\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/wiktorogrodnik/48/27498_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> WiktorOgrodnik:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>It could be achieved with e.g. <a href=\"https://github.com/KaTeX/KaTeX\">KaTeX project</a>, which is also written in JavaScript.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I‚Äôm not sure what you mean by ‚Äúalso‚Äù, but only the desktop client uses JavaScript. The iOS client is written in Swift and Objective-C, and the Android client is written in Java and Kotlin, which are entirely different.</p>\n<p>Related feature request for more general text formatting:</p><aside class=\"quote quote-modified\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"612\">\n  <div class=\"title\">\n    <div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n    <img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/failsafe/48/25300_2.png\" class=\"avatar\">\n    <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/font-styling-for-signal-messages-e-g-using-markdown/612\">Font styling for Signal messages</a> <a class=\"badge-category__wrapper \" href=\"/c/feature-requests/17\"><span data-category-id=\"17\" style=\"--category-badge-color: #83B72A; --category-badge-text-color: #FFFFFF;\" data-drop-close=\"true\" class=\"badge-category \" title=\"Post your ideas here for new features and functionality for the Signal app.\"><span class=\"badge-category__name\">Feature Requests</span></span></a>\n  </div>\n  <blockquote>\n    Is it possible to add font styling to signal only(non-sms) messages? \ni.e. Italicizing, Bold, Underlining etc. \n\nSuggested by <a class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/meteor0id\">@Meteor0id</a> : \n*Italic*\n_Italic_\n**Bold**\n__Bold__\n~Strike through~\n``*Escaped not italic*``\n```*Escaped not italic*```\n\nAnd an option in settings which will be enabled by default: \n\nEnable text styling \nWhen enabled text placed between asterisk or tilde symbols will be send italic, bold or with a strike through \n\nAlso note that escaped text should be treated like any othe‚Ä¶\n  </blockquote>\n</aside>\n",
