        "username": "Leptopoda",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/leptopoda/{size}/5476_2.png",
        "created_at": "2022-01-16T01:20:29.618Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Also latex is really slow and builds upon a single threaded cyclic rendering stack.</p>\n<p>This would result is really bad performance especially on mobile. I think it would be best to stick sending pre rendered content like a PDF or image.</p>\n<p>Also latex supports a lot of libraries of wich most used and publicly available are bundled in the texlive  project. All of them combined would be around 4GB.</p>\n<p>Also the biggest problem would be that this could lead to arbitrary remote code execution on the partners devices (unless ore rendered by the sender and sent as such) this would bring us back to the above mentioned solution.</p>",
