        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/anon53652/{size}/11044_2.png",
        "created_at": "2022-01-16T02:02:12.495Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote group-volunteer_moderators\" data-username=\"Leptopoda\" data-post=\"3\" data-topic=\"40878\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/leptopoda/48/5476_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> Leptopoda:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Also latex is really slow</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Bwoah, that was the case when I started with it on the 286 at the university. It became acceptable when I upgraded to a 486, and when I see how fast some quite heavy MathJax pages I put online (*) render on my phone I don‚Äôt think that would be a problem for messenger use. Unless you want to send whole books in LaTeX in a single message.</p>\n<p>(*) <a href=\"https://johanw.home.xs4all.nl/physics_html/index.html\" class=\"inline-onebox\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">Physics Formulary</a></p>",
