        "created_at": "2024-06-14T08:23:32.213Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I also want to throw in <a href=\"https://typst.app/\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">Typst</a> which is in many ways is a predecessor to LaTeX with many improvements, including the <a href=\"https://typst.app/docs/reference/math/\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">math typesetting</a> which is dramatically simplified. For instance, in LaTeX you have to do <code>$ \\frac{1}{2} $</code>. In Typst it‚Äôs just <code>$ 1/2 $</code>.</p>\n<p>It‚Äôs still growing, but I personally think that it will eventually replace LaTeX. Just like LaTeX has KaTeX, there‚Äôs <a href=\"https://github.com/0xpapercut/wypst\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">wypst</a> for Typst.</p>",
