        "created_at": "2024-06-14T08:51:28.493Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"melkster\" data-post=\"5\" data-topic=\"40878\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/melkster/48/29312_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> melkster:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>For instance, in LaTeX you have to do <code>$ \\frac{1}{2} $</code>. In Typst it‚Äôs just <code>$ 1/2 $</code>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I can do that in LaTeX too. I can choose how I want it formatted, up / below like with \\frac, or on the same line as with 1/2.</p>",
