        "id": 283660,
        "name": "Janneman84",
        "username": "Janneman84",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/janneman84/{size}/20115_2.png",
        "created_at": "2026-01-29T00:32:13.575Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I work on a chat app for students and I was tasked to show Latex code as equations inside chat bubbles. After some fiddling it turned out to be pretty doable. I managed to get it working in both native iOS (Swift) and native Android (Kotlin). Below an example screenshot:</p>\n<p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/e/b/eb2aa9d22501847c8c05d7d431b6506ebad1e078.png\" data-download-href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/eb2aa9d22501847c8c05d7d431b6506ebad1e078\" title=\"Scherm¬≠afbeelding 2026-01-28 om 13.23.43\"><img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/e/b/eb2aa9d22501847c8c05d7d431b6506ebad1e078_2_238x500.png\" alt=\"Scherm¬≠afbeelding 2026-01-28 om 13.23.43\" data-base62-sha1=\"xynBUb3TAE6nKvsHOV8t91u3tj2\" width=\"238\" height=\"500\" srcset=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/e/b/eb2aa9d22501847c8c05d7d431b6506ebad1e078_2_238x500.png, https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/e/b/eb2aa9d22501847c8c05d7d431b6506ebad1e078_2_357x750.png 1.5x, https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/e/b/eb2aa9d22501847c8c05d7d431b6506ebad1e078.png 2x\" data-dominant-color=\"ECD06B\"><div class=\"meta\"><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\">Scherm¬≠afbeelding 2026-01-28 om 13.23.43</span><span class=\"informations\">472√ó988 82.8 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>\n<p>I use a package that creates images of equations from Latex code. Then I add these images inside the text where the Latex codes used to be. The biggest challenge was to align the baseline of the equations to the baseline of the text.</p>\n<p>So I:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>use regex to find Latex codes inside the text</li>\n<li>use the package to generate equation images from those codes</li>\n<li>use some (nasty) trickery to determine the baseline of the equation</li>\n<li>replace the Latex codes with these images with correctly adjusted vertical offsets</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Performance is fine too. You might experience a small stutter when you have like 10 equations in one message like in the screenshot. Even this should be avoidable with some clever pre-render and caching strategies.</p>\n<p>I‚Äôd be more than happy to provide more details if interested.</p>",
